    retrieve or place a loom file for Grun/Muraro's pancreas study in BiocFileCache

    get_panc_loom_path.Rd

    retrieve or place a loom file for Grun/Muraro's pancreas study in BiocFileCache

    get_panc_loom_path(cache = BiocFileCache::BiocFileCache())

    Arguments

    cache

    instance of BiocFileCache::BiocFileCache()

    Value

    character path to loom file

    Note

    A loom file was distributed at https://figshare.com/articles/dataset/Data_used_for_demo_of_the_code_accompanying_the_i_Assessing_the_limits_of_zero-shot_foundation_models_in_single-cell_biology_i_paper_/24747228 under data/datasets/geneformer/pancreas_scib. The relevant publication seems to be https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/27345837/, GSE81076, etc.

    Examples

    pa = get_panc_loom_path()
proc = basilisk::basiliskStart(BiocGF:::gfenv)
x = basilisk::basiliskRun(proc, function() {
 anndata::read_loom(pa)
})
basilisk::basiliskStop(proc)
x
#> AnnData object with n_obs × n_vars = 16382 × 16388
#>     obs: 'adata_order', 'batch', 'celltype', 'n_counts', 'n_genes', 'n_genes_by_counts', 'obs_names', 'size_factors', 'tech', 'total_counts'
#>     var: 'ensembl_id', 'gene_symbols', 'has_ensembl_match', 'mean_counts', 'n_cells', 'n_cells_by_counts', 'pct_dropout_by_counts', 'total_counts', 'var_names'
#>     layers: 'counts'
